Hobey Baker, Sr., was captain of the Princeton football team in 1913.

LOC --- My poll of Google entries indicates that Baker's first name, when spelled with a &quot;y&quot;, invariably precedes it with an &quot;e&quot;, thus: &quot;Hobey Baker.&quot;

However, Google entries often spell it without a &quot;y&quot;: &quot;Hobie.&quot; I found an old New York Times story with this spelling.

BUT -- nobody but Bain's incompetent scribe ever spelled it &quot;Hoby.&quot;

I'm just sayin' . . . .
